cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new method for refining salient regions, which involves incorporating attention masks and a boundary refinement loss. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on several datasets, indicating that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
